Opposition sources in Cameroon said government soldiers were responsible for the burning down of a hospital in the restive South-West region. At least three people were reportedly burned alive. Video on social media shows the entire building in the town of Kumba ablaze. There have been previous reports of soldiers targeting hospitals in the belief that Anglophone separatist fighters were being treated there. A rebel leader, Chris Anu, said several nurses and a security guard had been abducted.  Dozens of Fleeing Nigerians Soldiers from Cameroon  Arrived Mubi Army confirms clash with Boko Haram at Cameroonian border Escapees tell of distress within B/Haram